
[1]therapeutic

   THERAPEU'TIC, a. [Gr. to nurse, serve or cure.] Curative; that pertains
   to the healing art; that is concerned in discovering and applying
   remedies for diseases.

   Medicine is justly distributed into prophylactic, or the art of
   preserving health, and therapeutic, or the art of restoring it.
